cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or dataset, please cite our paper."
title: "Natural System Reasoning in LLMs: Insights from the identification problem"
abstract: >
  A benchmark repository for studying rule and noise-parameter identification
  in Elementary Cellular Automata (ECA) under four distinct noise models
  (alpha-asynchronous, s-skewed, stochastic, temporal stochastic), using
  both purpose-built transformer architectures and large language models.
  Evaluating Qwen, Llama, Mixtral families (7-72B parameters) alongside
  frontier models under zero-shot, few-shot, and fine-tuned settings, we
  find near-perfect knowledge accuracy but poor task performance. We design
  four specialised transformer models (skewM, alphaM, stocM, tempM) achieving
  up to 99.22% rule exact match and 96.97% noise tolerance accuracy with
  at most 6.02M parameters.
